{{ typescaleTable(tokens.text.heading) }}

{{ heading('Tokens', '2') }}
{{ heading('Semantic', '3') }}
<p>Semantic text tokens reference the core font scales and give them purpose. Rather than applying raw scale values directly, semantic tokens map to the typescale variants used across Vivid — making it straightforward to apply consistent typography throughout the system.</p>

{{ heading('Composite tokens', '4') }}
<p>Each typescale variant has its own <strong>composite token</strong> — for example, <code>text-heading-xl</code> — that bundles all five typographic properties (font family, size, weight, line height, and stretch) into a single value mapping to the CSS <code>font</code> shorthand. Individual sub-tokens are also available for every property, so you can reference or override just one aspect of a style — for example <code>text-heading-font-weight-bold</code> or <code>text-body-sm-line-height</code> — without re-specifying the rest.</p>

